==English==
===Adjective===
{{wikipedia}}
'''psychedelic'''
# of, containing or generating [[hallucination]]s, [[distortion]]s of [[perception]], [[altered]] [[awareness]] etc

===Noun===
'''psychedelic'''
# any [[psychoactive]] substance (such as [[LSD]] or [[Psilocybin]]) which, when [[consume|consumed]], causes [[perception|perceptual]] changes (sometimes [[erratic]] and [[uncontrollable]]),  [[hallucination|Open and/or Closed Eye Visuals]],  and [[altered]] [[awareness]] of the [[body]] and [[mind]]. Psychedelics are not [[physically]] or [[mentally]] [[addictive]] due to the large amount of [[tolerance]] to the effects gained in a short period of time. Many [[drugs]] that are actually [[psychoactive]] are [[incorrect]]ly [[labeled]] as psychedelics, whereas psychedelics include very few or no [[stimulant]]s or [[dissociative]]s, and [[psychoactive]] is a '''much''' more [[general]] term.

===Interjection===
'''psychedelic'''!
#(1960s Hippy slang) [[awesome]], [[cool]], [[groovy]]

